INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '3b76d926-7b2c-4d88-89fa-13c57aaa1520',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$nmap - Crafting Effective Security Reports with CVSS Scoring$escape$,
  $escape$When scanning a target with nmap, it's essential to document findings using the NSE (Nmap Scripting Engine) output format. This format includes vulnerability information, services, and OS detection. Use the following nmap command to enable detailed output: `-sV --script=vuln --script-args=nmap-services`.

Next, use the CVSS (Common Vulnerability Scoring System) calculator to assign a score to each vulnerability based on attack vector, attack complexity, privileges required, user interaction, and impact. You can use the `cvss` NSE script to retrieve CVSS scores from NVD (National Vulnerability Database).

Finally, provide remediation recommendations in your report. This may include updating vulnerable software, patching systems, or implementing additional security controls. Always prioritize critical vulnerabilities and provide clear, actionable advice for the target's owners.$escape$,
  $escape$nmap -sV --script=vuln --script-args=nmap-services -oG -$escape$,
  $escape$bash$escape$,
